 Discuss the use of <script> tag in HTML. How can you link an external JavaScript file to an HTML document?


    -> Creating an external javascript file with "name.js" extension and writing JavaScript code in it.
    -> link the external JavaScript file to the HTML document using the <script> tag with the src attribute.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset='utf-8'>
    <meta http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible' content='IE=edge'>
    <title>Page Title</title>
    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1'>
    <link rel='stylesheet' type='text/css' media='screen' href='main.css'>

    <script src="main.js"></script>   -> linking an external JavaScript file

</head>
<body>
    
    // JavaScript code goes here

</body>
</html>


